<br>
Draw just the basic human body from the front to get your fell with it.  Only when you feel comfortable begin experementing.<br>
<br>
Take the head as a measurment for the whole body.  You see a manga body is 7 heads high.  My typical drawing has a head 3cm long so the rest of my body drawing never jumps the 21 cm in lenght (7x3).  These are simple calculations which can help you a lot to build a good stick figure which is the basis of a good body drawing.  <br>
<br>
I always try every part of the body out.  Do not be afraid to try hands, feet, eyes.  By hiding them after other body parts you will never learn.<br>
<br>
If you have any difficulties during the drawing.  First try it out and then post in the &quot;art in progress&quot; but first try it youself and do not worry if it comes wrong.<br>
<br>
Well hope it helps.  It sure did for me when I started.  <p><a href="http://www.geocities.com/vellj001"><img 
